-- Total, Chevron, BP, Statoil accept Venezuela deal
-- 
-- Mon Jun 25, 2007 1:31pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/25/us-venezuela-nationalization-signing-idUSN2530246520070625

 

 CARACAS  (Reuters) - Oil companies BP Plc ( BP.L ), Chevron Corp. ( CVX.N ), Total ( TOTF.PA ) and Statoil ( STL.OL ) have agreed to sign a deal on Monday with Venezuela for the state takeover of a majority stake in multibillion dollar oil projects, a government source told Reuters on Monday. 

